      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You should absolutely present the opposing view, but frame it as a necessary counterpoint to strengthen your main argument. Acknowledging the proceduralist interpretation shows students that the concept is debated, which is a key part of civics. However, immediately pivot back to the substantive view, emphasizing that the expansion of rights is the *correct* and most important application of the doctrine.",
      "source": "target",
