    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see what you mean about framing it. But I'm a little worried—if I spend too much time on the idea that it's just about 'fair procedures' and 'legal rules,' it might make the concept look like a technicality rather than a moral necessity. Is there a way to explain the proceduralist side without making it sound like they're just trying to undermine fundamental rights?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
