      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You can briefly mention the procedural view by labeling it as the narrow, technical reading of the law. Frame it as the argument that focuses only on *how* the government acts, not *what* the government is allowed to do to people. This allows you to dismiss it as a limited interpretation that fails to capture the true, expansive moral purpose of the Fourteenth Amendment.",
      "source": "target",
